quran[8]{c,v,t}:
  8,62,"For<i class=""s"">(even) </i>if they want to deceive you, then surely Allah is enough for you. It is He who aided you with His support{1}and with the believers.",footnotes:1:The Arabic word used for support isnasr which also means ‘victory’.
  8,63,"And He attuned their hearts. Had you spent whatever is in the earth, all together, you would not have attuned their hearts, but Allah attuned them. Indeed, He is Almighty, All-Wise."
  8,64,"O Prophet, Allah is sufficient for you and the believers who have followed you."
  8,65,"O Prophet, urge the believers on to combat. If there are twenty patient ones among you, they can overcome two hundred. And if there are a hundred of you, they can overcome a thousand of those who have denied, because they are a people who do not comprehend."
  8,66,"Now Allah has lightened your<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>burden and He has recognized that there <span class=""h"">is weakness in<sup foot_note=""80142"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>you. So if there are a hundred patient ones among you, they can overcome two hundred. And if there are a thousand of you, they can overcome two thousand by Allah’s leave. For Allah is with the patient ones."
  8,67,"Never would it befit any prophet to<i class=""s"">(stop the battle and) </i>take captives before he has subjugated<i class=""s"">(the enemy) </i>in the battlefield. You<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>want the materials of the Earlier<i class=""s"">(Life) </i>, but Allah wants the Hereafter. For Allah is Almighty, All-Wise."
  8,68,"Were it not for a predetermined decree from Allah, a great punishment would have befallen you for what you have taken."
  8,69,"So consume of what you have gained, legitimate and good, and be mindful of Allah. Indeed, Allah is Oft-Forgiving, Bestowing of mercy."
